Global Funds Buy Net 235 million Rupees of India Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-02-16T03:45:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/global-funds-buy-net-235-million-rupees-of-india-derivatives.html
Global investors bought a net 235.4
million rupees ($5.2 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, climbed 2 percent to 1.03 trillion rupees, or 34
percent of gross market position, according to the exchangeâ€™s
website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on
Sept. 21.  Foreign funds bought a net 2.33 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
